        %h2 A New International Photography Fair
    .row
      .span6
        %p 
          Unseen is an international photography fair giving new photography the platform it deserves. Unseen is a meeting place for young photographic talent and known photographers exhibiting new work, for galleries that focus on new developments and a global audience interested in the contemporary world of photography. With a focus on all that is ‘emerging’ in the world of photography, Unseen juxtaposes new work of established photographers and work of a new generation of young photographers. More than 50 contemporary art and photography galleries from around the world will participate in this first edition of Unseen.
          %span.italic
            See 
            =link_to("Galleries", Page.find_by_slug("galleries") || "#")
            page for a list of participating galleries.
      .span6
        %p Unseen will take place from September 19 to 23 in Amsterdam’s Westergasfabriek cultural park, a former gasworks site dating back to 1885. Surrounded by an expansive park, the 19th-century buildings house numerous creative spaces, restaurants, bars and a cinema.
        %p Unseen challenges the conventional photography fair. The look and layout of Unseen will bring out the best of contemporary photography. The industrial and interior design agency, Müller van Tol, has created a carrousel-like floor plan for the circular hall of the Gashouder. The Gashouder is a 60 meter diameter hall with 14 meter high ceilings, and will host around 50 gallery stands, a restaurant and bar, and a central pavilion that offers visitors a panoramic view of the fair.
