        %p Amsterdam is the home base of Unseen. With its progressive galleries and renowned art academies, the city offers a fruitful foundation for the arts. Amsterdam and Unseen share an international orientation, with a mentality that blends creativity, innovation and a mercantile spirit. The city stimulates an experimental atmosphere, and is the perfect place for the development of international creative talent.
        %p September is the start of the cultural season in the Netherlands, and the city of Amsterdam will host a range of art- and photography-related events. Highlights include the contemporary art fair Art Amsterdam 2012, that will be held in the north of Amsterdam (20-23 September), the much-anticipated opening of the Stedelijk Museum, and an Unseen-related exhibition at the photography museum Foam.
        %p In partnership with the city, we will organize Unseen Amsterdam, a programme of special events taking place at various cultural institutions, restaurants, bars and nightspots. An online Unseen Amsterdam city guide will provide tips on making the most out of your stay from 19 to 23 September.
